1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,360
=Episode 12=

3
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:41,510
My brother's been supporting me
since he started working.

4
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:46,270
But it's not like he makes much
on a fixed salary.

5
00:01:47,470 --> 00:01:49,630
His own family can barely
put food on the table.

6
00:01:50,030 --> 00:01:51,359
My sister-in-law threatened

7
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,880
to leave him and take the kids.

8
00:01:53,110 --> 00:01:54,919
But my sister talked her out of it.

9
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:57,120
She said she'd take over

10
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,840
supporting me.

11
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,990
But she's just
a regular employee herself.

12
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,480
It's not like she's rich.

13
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:09,230
Her husband was struggling,
but he never said it.

14
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:11,200
Her mother-in-law looked down on her.

15
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:15,390
Their home was a constant battlefield.

16
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:18,159
They barely managed to keep me
afloat until graduation.

17
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,790
Finally, I could start working.

18
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,110
I actually landed a pretty good job.

19
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,390
The family was finally seeing some hope.

20
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:29,070
My dad could finally hold his head high.

21
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:32,560
It was finally my turn
to pay my siblings back.

22
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:35,480
They always saw me as their star.

23
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,279
They poured everything they had
into me for over twenty years.

24
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,239
Just waiting for the day

25
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,440
I'd make it big and save
the whole family.

26
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:44,000
And then?

27
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,760
This is what I have to tell them.

28
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:55,029
(Medical Assessment: Hemodialysis,
Kidney Transplant)

29
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:56,320
I'm not going to make it.

30
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:02,160
I have to tell them I'm not their star.

31
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:05,349
I have to tell them

32
00:03:05,350 --> 00:03:08,110
I'm just a black hole,
sucking the family dry.

33
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,040
Just go home.

34
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,160
Just leave me alone.

35
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:25,909
This morning,

36
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:27,559
Feng Shengli collapsed in the street.

37
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,720
He was found and rushed to the hospital.

38
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:32,070
That's why we couldn't reach him.

39
00:03:32,510 --> 00:03:34,069
So he has uremia

40
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:35,279
just like the father?

41
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,160
That's quite a coincidence.

42
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,069
Does Feng Shengli's family

43
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:41,230
know about his condition?

44
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,790
He kept them completely in the dark.

45
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,959
He'd rather have them

46
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,629
think he's a deadbeat son

47
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:48,350
than let them know

48
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,309
the family's only hope

49
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,790
has already been crushed.

50
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,439
It looks like

51
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,200
this won't solve his problems.

52
00:03:56,790 --> 00:03:57,679
All right.

53
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,999
Shu Jing, Danian,

54
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,749
get in touch with Feng Lianshan

55
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,670
and Feng Shengli's' brother and sister.

56
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,439
Understood?

57
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,909
And Xiezhi...

58
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:06,510
Until we hear from the family,

59
00:04:06,790 --> 00:04:08,189
I'll stay at the hospital

60
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:10,349
just in case Feng Shengli
disappears again.

61
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:11,830
Very well.

62
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:25,440
(Mediation Room 1)

63
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:27,760
Dad, we're here.

64
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:33,510
Dad.

65
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,799
My dad is already this sick.

66
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,560
Why must you drag him here?

67
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:42,119
I called your whole family here today

68
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,679
because I wanted to talk face-to-face,

69
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,069
especially with you, sir,

70
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,679
to understand your demands.

71
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:47,309
Are you sure...

72
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,039
Positive.

73
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,679
He has to pay 350,000 yuan.

74
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,030
Not a cent less.

75
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,599
What about me?

76
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,949
What about my son?

77
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,439
You should

78
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,920
have him go to the hospital for an exam.

79
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,590
Dad.

80
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:04,030
Forget ever raising this kid.

81
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,309
We need to get the money
for your treatment first.

82
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:08,000
Your health comes first.

83
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,479
If Shengli pays the 350,000 yuan,

84
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,039
will that be enough for your treatment?

85
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,240
No.

86
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:16,000
I told you last time.

87
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,479
Between the surgery

88
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,949
and the recovery,

89
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:21,240
it's going to cost
about 500,000 yuan total.

90
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,679
But right now,

91
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,829
the two of us only have
about 30,000 to 50,000 yuan.

92
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:26,360
So from here on out,

93
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,360
we have to take it one step at a time.

94
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:31,200
We'll borrow more
from friends and relatives.

95
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:34,710
If my brother donates his kidney,

96
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,070
then I'll just work a few extra jobs.

97
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,359
And what if your generation

98
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,070
gets sick?

99
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,360
Don't you worry about that.

100
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,829
Don't let appearances fool you.

101
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:45,189
We're perfectly healthy.

102
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:45,949
It's fine.

103
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:47,799
Right, you two are fine.

104
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,920
But...

105
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,800
Judge.

106
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,120
Please, don't stop there.

107
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,240
Is my son sick?

108
00:05:55,710 --> 00:05:57,120
Where is he?

109
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:58,269
Tell him to come here.

110
00:05:58,270 --> 00:05:58,999
I need to see him.

111
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,919
Dad, he's not coming.

112
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,510
He's just putting on an act.

113
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,070
Calm down, sir.

114
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,239
Why do you think

115
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,879
that he's sick?

116
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,150
Well,

117
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,269
when he came back
before the Chinese New Year,

118
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:13,590
he was always

119
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,829
taking medicine in secret.

120
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:17,000
Medicine?

121
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,709
That medicine was called...

122
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:21,270
I couldn't read the label.

123
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:23,830
So I took a photo of it.

124
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,149
Dad.

125
00:06:26,150 --> 00:06:27,390
Take a look.

126
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,600
(Roxadustat Capsules)

127
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,039
I had my neighbor, Old Yu's grandson,

128
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,630
look it up online.

129
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,440
He said

130
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,270
it's specifically for kidney disease.

131
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,919
I was wondering about it back then.

132
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:49,149
He doesn't even work outdoors.

133
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,629
But his face

134
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,390
was always so dark.

135
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,439
Like he was being slowly poisoned.

136
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,389
Sir,

137
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:58,389
you seem to have plenty of energy.

138
00:06:58,390 --> 00:07:00,760
You don't look like you're in
the late stages of uremia.

139
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:04,919
Dad,

140
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,320
you're not sick?

141
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,439
Why put on such a show
if you aren't sick?

142
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,949
Look at how worried your kids are.

143
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:12,999
They're a total wreck.

144
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,919
I'm even more worried than they are.

145
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,709
He's such a good kid.

146
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:18,390
If he's really sick...

147
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,359
I have to help him.

148
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,030
I just wanted the court

149
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,629
to force him to get
a checkup at the hospital.

150
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:26,599
Wait, Dad,

151
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,039
pulling a stunt like this

152
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:30,240
is just making our lives difficult.

153
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,510
Seriously.

154
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:34,950
You scared me to death.

155
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:38,440
Why would you do such a thing?

156
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:40,150
You...

157
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,710
If you wanted him to get a checkup,

158
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,749
there are plenty of other ways.

159
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:47,030
If he refuses to go,
what can any of you do?

160
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,320
Honestly.

161
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,119
Judge,

162
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:58,070
is my brother actually sick?

163
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,629
What...

164
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:05,270
What kind of illness does he have?

165
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,030
Uremia.

166
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,950
It's a beautiful sunny day.

167
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,189
Look at these.

168
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:21,359
My grandmother sent these apples

169
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,039
all the way from back home.

170
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,799
They're really sweet.
I'll leave them here.

171
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,389
I don't owe you anything anymore.

172
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,800
What are you doing here?

173
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:30,999
Case is closed, but we still
provide after-sales support.

174
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,789
Our firm offers the most
comprehensive service.

175
00:08:32,790 --> 00:08:35,320
And I'm our star lawyer.

176
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,400
Look,

177
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:40,549
take them back.

178
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:42,149
Our contract is over.

179
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:44,149
I don't have any more business for you.

180
00:08:44,150 --> 00:08:45,149
What's wrong?

181
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,789
Don't you like apples?

182
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:48,119
I looked into your condition.

183
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,479
Some fruits are too high

184
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,830
in potassium for you.

185
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,429
Things like hami melon,
oranges, or bananas

186
00:08:52,430 --> 00:08:53,429
are bad for you.

187
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:55,199
Apples are the best choice for you.

188
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,389
Here, have a sip of water.

189
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:58,470
I don't want any water. Take it back.

190
00:08:58,630 --> 00:09:00,160
Just get out!

191
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:02,599
Can you all just stay
out of my business?

192
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:05,070
I don't need anyone's sympathy.

193
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,999
I've already cut ties
with my friends, my coworkers,

194
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,029
and even my family.

195
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:08,719
Why?

196
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,629
I want to be left alone

197
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:11,920
so I can die in peace!

198
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:13,999
I'm begging you.

199
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,239
I appreciate you coming to see me,

200
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,710
but please just go.

201
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,079
Mr. Feng.

202
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,029
Please, calm down.

203
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,149
Whatever it is,

204
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:22,909
we can figure it out together, right?

205
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,599
Medicine is so advanced these days.

206
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,959
I'm sure you can be treated.

207
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,470
I have uremia.

208
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:31,079
Even if I get the surgery
and a new kidney,

209
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,750
how much longer do I really have?

210
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,320
Five years?

211
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,560
Ten?

212
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:37,200
Twenty?

213
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,389
Do we really have to lose everything

214
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:44,350
and end up buried in debt?

215
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:54,040
Give this money to them.

216
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,110
And tell them

217
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,599
to just give up on me.

218
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,400
I'm just a burden now.

219
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,200
You have to

220
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,920
give it to them yourself.

221
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,400
You have to

222
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:07,400
tell them yourself.

223
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,549
Leave. Just go!

224
00:10:11,550 --> 00:10:13,640
Get out!

225
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:15,199
Out!

226
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,320
Mr. Feng.

227
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:17,950
I'm leaving.

228
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:20,429
Where are you going?

229
00:10:20,430 --> 00:10:21,560
Take it easy.

230
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,119
Feng Shengli!

231
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,280
What are you doing?

232
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:27,590
Shengli!

233
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,590
Shengli! He's coming out!

234
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:31,429
Shengli!

235
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:32,440
Shengli!

236
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:36,909
Oh no.

237
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:38,070
Shengli!

238
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,590
Good, you're just in time.

239
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,479
Here is your 350,000 yuan.

240
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,320
Give me the receipt right now.

241
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:52,789
After this, we go our separate ways.

242
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,440
Don't ever ask me for money again.

243
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,350
Feng Shengli!

244
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:05,710
Why are you still acting like this?

245
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:09,320
Why would you lie to us?

246
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:11,470
Why didn't you tell us you were sick?

247
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,470
There are three of us here.

248
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:16,070
That's six kidneys between us.

249
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,389
How can we not spare just one for you?

250
00:11:18,390 --> 00:11:19,920
Alright, that's enough. Get up.

251
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,440
Shengli.

252
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:23,029
Are you worried about the money?

253
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:24,079
Let me tell you something.

254
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,079
For major diseases,

255
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,199
insurance should cover
most of the costs.

256
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,870
If it doesn't, we can always
start a fundraiser online.

257
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,959
No matter how much debt you're in,

258
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,509
your sister and I will help you.

259
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:35,950
We are not going to let this beat us.

260
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:38,750
Son.

261
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,640
If you're sick,

262
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,870
get the right treatment.

263
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:44,990
And if it comes down to it,

264
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:46,640
I'll give you one of

265
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:48,640
my own kidneys.

266
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,070
Dad.

267
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:52,920
I know you all mean well.

268
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,149
But I'm not doing the treatment.

269
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:57,149
Just go home and live your own lives.

270
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:59,320
I've already been
a burden for thirty years.

271
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:02,599
I won't let your families be
torn apart because of me.

272
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,640
Who says our families are
being torn apart?

273
00:12:05,630 --> 00:12:07,230
If this is about your sister-in-law,

274
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,079
she's fine.

275
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,710
She might scream
about divorce every day,

276
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,479
but she could never
actually leave our brother.

277
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:15,029
She loves him too much.

278
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,029
As long as he's not the donor,

279
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,719
she won't have a problem with anything.

280
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,160
What are you talking about?

281
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:21,749
If I don't do it, who will?

282
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,389
He's my little brother.

283
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:25,599
Brother, just stop arguing.

284
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:28,029
You make more money than I do,
so let me be the donor.

285
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:29,549
We need you working
to pay them back.

286
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:30,629
He's a grown man.

287
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:32,160
He can't have a woman's kidney.

288
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,680
Feng Shengli!

289
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,149
Shengli!

290
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:38,040
Shengli!

291
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:41,959
Feng Shengli!

292
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:42,749
Stay back!

293
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,909
Don't come any closer!

294
00:12:43,910 --> 00:12:45,280
Just stay right there!

295
00:12:45,630 --> 00:12:46,920
Take it easy.

296
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,950
We can talk this through, okay?

297
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:50,599
Dad.

298
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,800
Sister.

299
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:52,920
Brother.

300
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,640
Just listen to me.

301
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,870
Give up on me.

302
00:12:57,630 --> 00:12:58,990
It's not worth it.

303
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:01,280
It's not worth it anymore.

304
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:03,110
Yeah.

305
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,990
Only I went to college.

306
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,640
But my sister was at the top
of her class every year.

307
00:13:10,670 --> 00:13:11,669
She dropped out to work

308
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:12,920
because of me.

309
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,560
If we actually had any money,

310
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:17,389
there's no way

311
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:19,110
I'd be the only one with a degree.

312
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,710
And Brother,

313
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,400
I remember.

314
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,350
I haven't forgotten a thing.

315
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:28,280
I used the money meant for your wedding
to pay for my tuition.

316
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,389
If it wasn't for me, you and...

317
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:31,520
That's enough.

318
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,839
We did all that for you
because we wanted to.

319
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,879
I wasn't talented like you.

320
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,830
I couldn't get into a top university,

321
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:40,199
land a job at a major firm,

322
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,959
or make it in the big city.

323
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,470
But so what?

324
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:45,719
They made up an excuse

325
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,879
to demote me

326
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,350
when they found out I was sick.

327
00:13:48,390 --> 00:13:49,239
Look at me now.

328
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,680
Does this look like
I made it in the city?

329
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,520
All these years,

330
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:57,710
I thought about getting married.

331
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,029
But the moment
any matchmakers or dates

332
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:03,230
heard about our family situation,

333
00:14:03,630 --> 00:14:04,959
they turned cold instantly.

334
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,479
I didn't want to be a burden to anyone.

335
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:09,040
Everyone wants an easy life, don't they?

336
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,040
There's no point in forcing it.

337
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:18,719
A guy like me could never afford
a house or a car in Tianhai.

338
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:21,149
I could never afford
to start a family here.

339
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:22,269
If I did get married,

340
00:14:22,270 --> 00:14:23,119
and had kids to raise

341
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,199
while taking care of my family,

342
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,599
what then?

343
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:28,350
One emergency would wipe out
every cent I made.

344
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,199
I don't blame them for rejecting me.

345
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,719
Anyone would be terrified of this life.

346
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,950
Son,

347
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,950
we don't want your money.

348
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,879
As long as you can get better,

349
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,359
you don't have to worry about me.

350
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,640
How can I not worry? You're my father.

351
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,680
I'm nothing but a burden.

352
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:49,239
I'm a burden to everyone,
to my family, to society.

353
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,199
I'm a liability.

354
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,359
If I hadn't come along,

355
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,629
this family wouldn't be in this mess.

356
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:55,719
But you're the successful one.

357
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,990
You earned all those scholarships.

358
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,590
Those were just grants.

359
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,680
Financial aid for students
who had to work.

360
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,389
It was just my vanity.
I hate myself for it.

361
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:07,629
I only said that because
I was too ashamed to tell the truth.

362
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,870
No!

363
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,719
I finally landed a job.

364
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,870
Forget about me paying you back.

365
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:18,470
Now I'm supposed
to take your kidneys too?

366
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:20,269
And keep living off your
hard-earned money?

367
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:21,640
I can't do that!

368
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,870
Yeah.

369
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:25,590
My brother-in-law and
sister-in-law are good people.

370
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,710
They haven't complained.

371
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,520
But why should they?

372
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,509
Why should they spend their whole lives

373
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:33,359
suffering for a burden like me?

374
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,680
How is that fair?

375
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,319
Feng Shengli.

376
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,830
I get where you're coming from.

377
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,440
I grew up in a village, just like you.

378
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,470
The two of us...

379
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,479
We're not the same.

380
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,990
How so?

381
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,269
Do you think society

382
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:53,319
has different expectations
for men and women?

383
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,070
That's just a stereotype.

384
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,429
You're an independent person.

385
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:58,389
You're a human being in your own right.

386
00:15:58,390 --> 00:15:59,549
Why do you have to bow down

387
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,280
to the labels people put on you?

388
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,350
Ms. Qin.

389
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:06,800
I'm sorry.

390
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,280
Brother.

391
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:11,750
Sister.

392
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,520
I'm so sorry.

393
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,040
Dad.

394
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:19,320
I let you down.

395
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,590
Don't say that, Shengli.

396
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:39,359
(It was right there.)

397
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,269
(The blade was almost touching my face.)

398
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,839
I panicked. I thought,

399
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:43,359
"What now?"

400
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,999
"I've spent over a decade
in this industry."

401
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,509
"I'm getting disfigured before I even

402
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:47,749
make a name for myself?"

403
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,029
"How would I land another client?"

404
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:51,400
You're seriously reckless.

405
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:53,389
You threw yourself

406
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,549
on Mr. Zhou's car.

407
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:56,560
Now you're charging at the knife?

408
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,479
With so many people there,

409
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,959
couldn't they have
figured something out?

410
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,280
Why must you jump in?

411
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,040
I was the closest to him.

412
00:17:04,710 --> 00:17:06,079
It was pure instinct.

413
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:07,640
I was as stunned as everyone else.

414
00:17:09,190 --> 00:17:10,319
Tell me more.

415
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:12,120
How exactly did Xiezhi save you?

416
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:14,079
Did he pull you into his arms

417
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:15,279
and then with his hand

418
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,880
grab the scissors?

419
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,880
Look at you.

420
00:17:22,150 --> 00:17:23,079
You were quietly

421
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:25,200
playing the hero for a pretty lady.

422
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,470
Don't tell me you've got a crush on her.

423
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,909
Feng Shengli was out of control

424
00:17:31,910 --> 00:17:33,550
and almost hurt someone.

425
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:35,319
Was I just supposed to watch?

426
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,279
No.

427
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:38,120
But why use your hand as a shield?

428
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:40,119
You saw she was about to get hurt

429
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,470
and you panicked.

430
00:17:42,430 --> 00:17:44,279
Do you even know me?

431
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,359
I would've done the same
for a total stranger.

432
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,599
Stop taking the high ground with me.

433
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,710
You're just dodging the question
like a slick.

434
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:50,909
Take my advice.

435
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:52,840
Get the hospital's security footage.

436
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,510
The footage? What for?

437
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,640
To save it.

438
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:00,389
Then when you two get married,

439
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:01,669
you can have it playing

440
00:18:01,670 --> 00:18:03,950
on a massive screen at the wedding.

441
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:05,229
Just loop it.

442
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,120
Can you imagine the vibe?

443
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:08,990
It'll make me believe in love again.

444
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:10,709
Shen Xiezhi is a judge.

445
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:12,759
He was being helpful

446
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,709
and protecting a citizen.

447
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:16,039
He'd do the same for anyone.

448
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:18,120
Please, my dear friend.

449
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,469
Think about it.

450
00:18:19,470 --> 00:18:21,519
There are a dozen ways to save someone.

451
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,640
He could've just pulled you away

452
00:18:23,950 --> 00:18:25,389
or held you back instead.

453
00:18:25,390 --> 00:18:28,470
Why did he have to jump in
and take the hit?

454
00:18:29,990 --> 00:18:31,189
Maybe

455
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:33,360
I just saw it wrong
because of the angle.

456
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,840
I've heard you tell this story
three times now.

457
00:18:37,910 --> 00:18:39,229
And that one detail

458
00:18:39,230 --> 00:18:40,550
hasn't changed once.

459
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,469
Trust me.

460
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:46,230
Human beings are wired
for self-preservation.

461
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:47,909
His natural reflex

462
00:18:47,910 --> 00:18:49,600
should've been to dodge the blade.

463
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:52,030
It must have hurt, right?

464
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,389
This just proves

465
00:18:54,390 --> 00:18:56,279
that his urge to protect you

466
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,470
was stronger
than his own survival instinct.

467
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:00,469
It was just a reflex.

468
00:19:00,470 --> 00:19:02,790
Saving someone happens
in a split second.

469
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:04,279
Purely instinct.

470
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:05,989
Well, if we're getting into biology,

471
00:19:05,990 --> 00:19:07,600
that's way over my head.

472
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:10,319
Maybe I'll just ask Liu Lian.

473
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,759
Since they're roommates,

474
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,550
she probably knows more than I do.

475
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,119
You really have

476
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,389
no boundaries these days.

477
00:19:16,390 --> 00:19:17,640
Put that phone down.

478
00:19:17,910 --> 00:19:20,039
To deal with someone of your character,

479
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:21,840
this is necessary.

480
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:28,080
I didn't want her to get hurt.

481
00:19:28,430 --> 00:19:29,709
So I used my arm to block it.

482
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:31,790
Anyone would've done the same.

483
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:32,949
There's nothing between us.

484
00:19:32,950 --> 00:19:34,230
Nothing?

485
00:19:34,470 --> 00:19:35,319
Really.

486
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,469
Are you sure about that?

487
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:37,550
Positive.

488
00:19:51,850 --> 00:19:57,580
♪When a leaf can't find a place to fall♪

489
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,880
(There are a dozen ways
to save someone.)

490
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:01,839
(He could've)

491
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,200
(just pulled you away)

492
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,799
(or held you back instead.)

493
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,979
(Why did he have to jump in
and take the hit?)

494
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:12,060
♪Until you appear and I see your eyes♪

495
00:20:12,970 --> 00:20:14,599
♪I've decided♪

496
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:17,760
♪To stay by your side♪

497
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:18,879
(You were quietly)

498
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,920
(playing the hero for a pretty lady.)

499
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:22,909
(You saw she was about to get hurt)

500
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:24,160
(and you panicked.)

501
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:33,010
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

502
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:37,359
♪I want to be in your world♪

503
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:40,229
♪And cast away my disguise♪

504
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:41,359
(I wonder how he is.)

505
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,600
(Shen Xiezhi)

506
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,229
(Is his wound serious?)

507
00:20:44,230 --> 00:20:46,319
(I didn't even get to
thank him properly today.)

508
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:48,320
(Ms. Qin)

509
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,280
(Obsessed!)

510
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,120
She really makes the most of life.

511
00:20:55,470 --> 00:20:56,949
(She must have been terrified today.)

512
00:20:56,950 --> 00:20:58,400
(Should I check on her?)

513
00:20:59,670 --> 00:21:00,709
(Never mind.)

514
00:21:00,710 --> 00:21:01,999
(She might get the wrong idea.)

515
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,560
(Judge Shen,
is your injury feeling better?)

516
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:13,510
(Maybe just asking isn't enough.)

517
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:22,319
♪I'll be there for you
until the very end♪

518
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:26,360
(When are you free?
I'd like to come see you.)

519
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:28,949
(Actually, forget it.)

520
00:21:28,950 --> 00:21:31,600
(He'd just say judges and lawyers
need to keep their distance.)

521
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,400
(Qingcheng District)

522
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,790
(Those labels you toss,)

523
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,990
(whether compliments or insults,)

524
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,909
(make you think you've seen through)

525
00:21:57,910 --> 00:21:59,189
(a person's struggles.)

526
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:00,319
(But what you don't see)

527
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:02,400
(is that the person you're mocking)

528
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,189
(might be the hope of an entire family,)

529
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:05,949
(or even a whole lineage.)

530
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:10,160
(They emptied their savings and gambled
their future just to keep that hope alive.)

531
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,709
(That hope shines so bright,)

532
00:22:12,710 --> 00:22:14,470
(yet it's so incredibly fragile.)

533
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:17,120
(To find their footing
in a strange city,)

534
00:22:17,150 --> 00:22:18,879
(they quietly)

535
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,880
(prune away parts of themselves.)

536
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:23,920
(They strip away their rural accents)

537
00:22:23,990 --> 00:22:27,230
(and cut those
heavy ties to their past.)

538
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:30,310
(They bury themselves
in the rules of the city,)

539
00:22:30,360 --> 00:22:31,669
(desperate to fit in,)

540
00:22:31,670 --> 00:22:34,270
(all for a chance to grow.)

541
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:37,629
(However, the hidden dangers of life)

542
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:40,160
(don't care how much
you've sacrificed.)

543
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,470
(One serious illness)

544
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:43,759
(or one accident)

545
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:47,270
(is enough to watch
all that effort go down the drain.)

546
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:48,879
(I used to think)

547
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:50,840
(that was the worst it could get.)

548
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:52,759
(Until I was in Family Court,)

549
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:55,710
(where family bonds
are put to the test,)

550
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:58,750
(and love mends the cracks.)

551
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,599
(Now I finally believe)

552
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,080
(that no matter
how rough the road gets,)

553
00:23:03,230 --> 00:23:04,429
(there's always)

554
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,079
(one ray of light in this world)

555
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,359
(that shines just for love.)

556
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,600
One at a time, please.

557
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:12,360
Come on.

558
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:13,640
Did the scan go through?

559
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,949
Just tell me how much you're donating.

560
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:17,079
I've got 500 yuan here.

561
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:18,229
Han, 500 yuan.

562
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:19,469
Thank you

563
00:23:19,470 --> 00:23:21,440
for supporting Feng Shengli.

564
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:23,989
(My mentor always says)

565
00:23:23,990 --> 00:23:26,359
(that closing a case isn't just
about handing down a verdict.)

566
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:27,559
(As a judge,)

567
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:29,319
(Dan, Young Li, Old Li)
(if we don't get)

568
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:30,790
(to the bottom of things)

569
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:32,599
(to understand someone's struggle,)

570
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,079
(if we ignore even the smallest doubt)

571
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,950
(lingering in our hearts,)

572
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,680
(then what's waiting for him)

573
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:39,880
(might be a lonely death,)

574
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:42,950
(a life ending
in total despair and surrender.)

575
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,879
(A person's life or death)

576
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:48,839
(often depends on
whether we keep asking questions,)

577
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,519
(even if those questions)

578
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,119
(put us in unpredictable danger.)

579
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,629
(Qingcheng District People's Court)

580
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:56,510
Master, what's up?

581
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,279
Su Qi.

582
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:58,229
Were you just organizing

583
00:23:58,230 --> 00:24:00,279
the donations for Feng Shengli?

584
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,319
Yeah.

585
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:02,669
I meant to tell you,

586
00:24:02,670 --> 00:24:03,949
but it just slipped my mind.

587
00:24:03,950 --> 00:24:05,189
I was on a call,

588
00:24:05,190 --> 00:24:06,990
and I have to head out again in a bit.

589
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:09,559
How much did everyone give?

590
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:10,990
I gave 300 yuan.

591
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,839
Then I'll give 500 yuan.

592
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:13,229
Okay.

593
00:24:13,230 --> 00:24:14,079
I'll transfer it to you.

594
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,319
Got it, no problem.

595
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,429
You get back to it then.

596
00:24:16,430 --> 00:24:17,839
Alright, it's sent.

597
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:19,030
Okay.

598
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:22,400
Here.

599
00:24:26,150 --> 00:24:27,640
Thank you, Judge Shen.

600
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,470
Thanks to everyone at the court,

601
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,879
and to all the kind people out there.

602
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,750
We've received the donations.

603
00:24:33,950 --> 00:24:34,759
That's wonderful.

604
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,429
Sir,

605
00:24:35,430 --> 00:24:37,039
if anything else comes up,

606
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,550
you can reach out to us anytime.

607
00:24:41,230 --> 00:24:42,510
There he is.

608
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:44,469
How are you feeling?

609
00:24:44,470 --> 00:24:45,990
Is the recovery going okay?

610
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:47,550
Pretty good.

611
00:24:48,190 --> 00:24:50,310
You need to focus on getting better now.

612
00:24:50,390 --> 00:24:51,559
Everyone is waiting for you.

613
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:52,839
You've got a lot of favors to return,

614
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:54,440
so take your time.

615
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:55,559
Don't you worry.

616
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,799
I'm still alive.

617
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,920
If I ever need a lawyer,
I'm coming to you.

618
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:00,440
Give me a discount.

619
00:25:02,150 --> 00:25:03,149
As much as

620
00:25:03,150 --> 00:25:04,950
I'd love the business,

621
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:07,429
I hope the rest of your life is free

622
00:25:07,430 --> 00:25:09,160
of trouble, illness, and lawsuits.

623
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,160
Let's go.

624
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,359
Thank you so much.

625
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,750
It was the right thing to do.

626
00:25:18,430 --> 00:25:20,510
How are you doing, son?

627
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:21,599
I'm fine, really.

628
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,750
Judge Shen.

629
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:24,680
Good.

630
00:25:24,910 --> 00:25:26,200
Judge Shen.

631
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,600
Ms. Qin.

632
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,039
Judge Shen.

633
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,709
Is your wound getting better?

634
00:25:33,710 --> 00:25:35,040
(People's Hospital)
It's just a scratch.

635
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,680
It's almost healed. Nothing serious.

636
00:25:37,430 --> 00:25:38,710
I really

637
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,600
owe you a big one.

638
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,229
You were such a huge help.

639
00:25:42,230 --> 00:25:43,600
If it wasn't for you,

640
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:46,310
my client wouldn't have
raised the money so quickly.

641
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,920
It's all part of the job.

642
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:52,840
Now let's just hope
the surgery goes smoothly.

643
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:56,669
In the future,

644
00:25:56,670 --> 00:25:58,600
if there's anything I can do for you,

645
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:00,440
just let me know.

646
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:02,550
Not at the moment.

647
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:03,709
I know

648
00:26:03,710 --> 00:26:06,030
things are a bit sensitive between us.

649
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:09,310
I'm always looking
for work at Qingcheng Court,

650
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,680
so we keep running
into each other on cases.

651
00:26:12,710 --> 00:26:14,920
It's definitely not ideal
for us to meet in private.

652
00:26:15,990 --> 00:26:17,270
But

653
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,039
you literally took a blade for me,

654
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:20,429
and you helped us so much.

655
00:26:20,430 --> 00:26:22,360
You're my lifesaver now.

656
00:26:22,430 --> 00:26:23,669
Whenever you need a hand,

657
00:26:23,670 --> 00:26:24,389
just say the word.

658
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:26,710
I'd go through hell and back for you.

659
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,080
I appreciate that, Ms. Qin.

660
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:32,400
But

661
00:26:32,430 --> 00:26:34,359
our professional relationship

662
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:35,880
is a bit complicated.

663
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:37,799
We should keep our distance.

664
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,559
If a client saw us,

665
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:41,990
it'd cause a lot of unnecessary trouble.

666
00:26:42,990 --> 00:26:44,710
I understand.

667
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:48,440
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

668
00:26:51,390 --> 00:26:52,990
Goodbye, Judge Shen.

669
00:27:00,230 --> 00:27:00,989
Mom,

670
00:27:00,990 --> 00:27:03,149
when my big brother was in college,

671
00:27:03,150 --> 00:27:05,079
(Family Court)
how much did you and Dad lend him?

672
00:27:05,080 --> 00:27:06,640
Do you still have that notebook?

673
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:07,839
Mom,

674
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,600
Dad used to say

675
00:27:09,910 --> 00:27:11,879
that since the oldest was doing well,

676
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,319
we didn't have to worry about him.

677
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:14,149
This inheritance

678
00:27:14,150 --> 00:27:16,270
should be left to us younger ones.

679
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:20,360
I remember.

680
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:21,989
That's more like it.

681
00:27:21,990 --> 00:27:23,080
Exactly.

682
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:24,510
Judge.

683
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:25,759
You should hit the gavel.

684
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,229
They're asking leading questions

685
00:27:27,230 --> 00:27:28,790
to fish for testimony.

686
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:30,909
My grandfather didn't leave a will.

687
00:27:30,910 --> 00:27:33,750
My father never neglected
his duty to care for him.

688
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:36,270
It's true my dad is doing better now.

689
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:38,079
He doesn't care about the inheritance.

690
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:40,359
But the law isn't about robbing
the rich to give to the poor.

691
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,149
You should follow the principles

692
00:27:42,150 --> 00:27:44,629
of statutory succession to determine
the rightful heirs in the same order.

693
00:27:44,630 --> 00:27:46,759
Allocate the assets

694
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,360
based on the standard legal shares.

695
00:27:49,230 --> 00:27:51,310
A law student from CUPL?

696
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,080
Impressive.

697
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:54,799
I have three years
for my bachelor's.

698
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:56,599
Two for my master's
and three for my PhD.

699
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:58,990
I'll be back here
as a judge in eight years.

700
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:01,919
Court is adjourned.

701
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,880
(Law Brings Peace to the People)

702
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:11,080
Hello, Senior.

703
00:28:11,630 --> 00:28:12,669
It's alright.

704
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:13,559
What is it?

705
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,880
See you, Senior.

706
00:28:16,390 --> 00:28:18,510
Fine, see you in eight years.

707
00:28:18,670 --> 00:28:20,120
It's okay, get back to work.

708
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,510
Mentor.

709
00:28:23,710 --> 00:28:25,759
Did you really just rule
exactly the way he said?

710
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:26,879
Why wouldn't I?

711
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,200
The facts are clear.

712
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:29,519
The evidence is solid.

713
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:30,839
It's a textbook case.

714
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:32,310
How else was I supposed to rule?

715
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:36,359
He's very arrogant for a freshman.

716
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:37,519
And because of that,

717
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,510
he hasn't been hit by reality yet.

718
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:42,879
They all think they're the chosen ones

719
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,200
who can change the world.

720
00:28:45,430 --> 00:28:47,510
Let him work
in the courts for a few years.

721
00:28:48,150 --> 00:28:49,680
I might still be better than him.

722
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:53,440
He's like a newborn calf
with no fear of tigers.

723
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,599
No fear?

724
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,400
This kid wants to swallow the tiger.

725
00:28:58,630 --> 00:29:01,030
You think being
a Deputy Chief Judge is easy?

726
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:15,600
(Emergency: Family's only hope!
Uremia and kidney failure)

727
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:19,680
(Ding Yajing)

728
00:29:24,940 --> 00:29:25,709
Hello?

729
00:29:25,710 --> 00:29:26,990
Ms. Ding?

730
00:29:27,470 --> 00:29:28,710
Hi, Ms. Qin.

731
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:32,310
Your voice sounds off.

732
00:29:33,190 --> 00:29:34,229
It sounds a bit strange.

733
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,950
Are you okay?

734
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:38,510
No, it's nothing.

735
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:40,510
I just caught a cold.

736
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:42,950
As long as you're safe.

737
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:44,710
What's on your mind?

738
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:45,799
Well, the thing is,

739
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:47,030
Ms. Qin,

740
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:49,279
I'm going to be very busy next month.

741
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:51,920
Is there any way we could
move the hearing up?

742
00:29:52,630 --> 00:29:53,920
To an earlier date?

743
00:29:54,950 --> 00:29:57,400
Do you have something else
going on at that time?

744
00:29:58,150 --> 00:30:00,599
I'm being sent abroad for work.

745
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:02,470
And I really can't get out of it.

746
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:05,920
Well,

747
00:30:06,190 --> 00:30:08,230
I'll see what I can do, okay?

748
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:10,279
Ms. Qin, please, I'm counting on you.

749
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,680
You can't just try.
I really can't miss this trip.

750
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,470
Okay.

751
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,230
I'll find a way

752
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:18,709
to help you.

753
00:30:18,710 --> 00:30:19,840
Thank you so much.

754
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,990
What's the matter?

755
00:30:27,150 --> 00:30:28,550
Did the case fall through?

756
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:31,790
If only it were that simple,
I'd actually have some peace.

757
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,519
Ms. Ding wants me

758
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,120
to reschedule the hearing.

759
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,080
And?

760
00:30:38,190 --> 00:30:39,710
It's just that

761
00:30:40,150 --> 00:30:42,189
Judge Shen just took a blade for me.

762
00:30:42,190 --> 00:30:43,790
It feels wrong

763
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:45,400
to trouble him with this

764
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:47,160
at the moment.

765
00:30:47,190 --> 00:30:49,669
Your client has a legitimate request.

766
00:30:49,670 --> 00:30:51,189
Just ask him like you normally would.

767
00:30:51,190 --> 00:30:52,880
What's the big deal?

768
00:30:53,710 --> 00:30:55,640
Unless you've got a guilty conscience?

769
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,470
No way.

770
00:30:59,630 --> 00:31:01,080
I'll ask him.

771
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:04,629
(Honorable Judge,)

772
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:06,389
(my client, Ding Yajing,)

773
00:31:06,390 --> 00:31:07,839
(is being sent abroad for work,)

774
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:10,389
(which conflicts
with the current hearing date.)

775
00:31:10,390 --> 00:31:13,510
(We would like to request
an earlier date if possible.)

776
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:19,680
(It is currently after hours.
I cannot assist you right now.)

777
00:31:24,710 --> 00:31:25,469
(Ms. Qin,)

778
00:31:25,470 --> 00:31:27,279
(the hearing schedule is already set.)

779
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,669
(If the client has a conflict,)

780
00:31:28,670 --> 00:31:30,519
(you can file a formal application.)

781
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:32,039
(I'm fully booked at the moment,)

782
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:33,510
(so I can't move it up.)

783
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:37,640
I got a no from him.

784
00:31:38,230 --> 00:31:39,920
Short and professional.

785
00:31:41,190 --> 00:31:42,470
Let me see it.

786
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:45,990
Professional?

787
00:31:46,910 --> 00:31:48,709
You're the one being too formal.

788
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:50,669
He just calls you "Ms. Qin,"

789
00:31:50,670 --> 00:31:52,149
but you're writing

790
00:31:52,150 --> 00:31:54,920
"Honorable Judge."

791
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,230
True.

792
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:05,149
It was such short notice.

793
00:32:05,150 --> 00:32:06,920
I'd be surprised if he said yes.

794
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:13,469
Fei,

795
00:32:13,470 --> 00:32:15,039
are you ready to go?

796
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,039
I've got your orange juice

797
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:17,469
and soda all ready for you.

798
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:18,839
But I think

799
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:20,429
we should stick to the juice.

800
00:32:20,430 --> 00:32:22,119
Soda will make you burp,

801
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:24,550
and that'll ruin your performance, okay?

802
00:32:25,190 --> 00:32:26,599
Bring a thermos of hot water too.

803
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:27,799
I've got the thermos.

804
00:32:27,800 --> 00:32:28,629
I'll fill it there

805
00:32:28,630 --> 00:32:29,669
in case it leaks on the way.

806
00:32:29,670 --> 00:32:30,950
Give it here.

807
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,149
Just fill it before we leave.

808
00:32:34,150 --> 00:32:35,519
It's going to be packed there.

809
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:37,839
You'll just end up
leaving her alone again.

810
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:39,629
What if it leaks? Seriously.

811
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,160
Fei, are you done?

812
00:32:41,190 --> 00:32:41,759
Yes.

813
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:42,469
Come on.

814
00:32:42,470 --> 00:32:44,640
Let's get your backpack on.

815
00:32:46,950 --> 00:32:48,600
How long is the show?

816
00:32:48,670 --> 00:32:50,400
About three hours.

817
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:52,149
Fei,

818
00:32:52,150 --> 00:32:54,189
I have to finish
my quarterly report today.

819
00:32:54,190 --> 00:32:55,879
I'm too busy to go with you.

820
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,920
Daddy will help you
change into your costume.

821
00:32:57,990 --> 00:32:59,319
Backstage is going to be

822
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:00,599
full of little girls.

823
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:02,840
Do you really think it's okay for a guy
to go in there?

824
00:33:04,710 --> 00:33:06,519
Tell you what, I'll just come along.

825
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:08,079
I can finish my report there.

826
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,200
Okay.

827
00:33:09,670 --> 00:33:11,510
Alright, hurry up.

828
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:13,030
We're in a rush.

829
00:33:17,470 --> 00:33:18,790
Come in.

830
00:33:19,710 --> 00:33:21,400
I knew you'd be here.

831
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:22,799
Danian.

832
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,119
Out of tea again?
It's in the cabinet. Help yourself.

833
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:27,600
What kind of person do you take me for?

834
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:30,229
My wife made some panda cookies

835
00:33:30,230 --> 00:33:31,229
for everyone.

836
00:33:31,230 --> 00:33:32,550
They look pretty good.

837
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,279
Did you steal those from your kid?

838
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,519
No. We have more at home.

839
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,469
I've already handed out the rest.

840
00:33:38,470 --> 00:33:40,519
This bag is for you. Try one.

841
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:41,990
Alright then. Thanks.

842
00:33:44,190 --> 00:33:46,080
Thank your wife for me.

843
00:33:50,470 --> 00:33:51,710
Delicious.

844
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:54,920
Isn't this a case you handled
back in the early 2000s?

845
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,600
Writing your memoirs?

846
00:33:57,840 --> 00:33:59,149
What memoirs?

847
00:33:59,150 --> 00:34:00,400
Have a seat.

848
00:34:01,910 --> 00:34:02,709
With your experience,

849
00:34:02,710 --> 00:34:04,710
you really ought to write a memoir.

850
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,550
With my limited experience,

851
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,600
I'd be too embarrassed
to write a memoir.

852
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,600
It's just that

853
00:34:12,430 --> 00:34:13,960
since I'm retiring soon,

854
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,679
I wanted to look back

855
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:17,710
at the cases I've handled
over the years.

856
00:34:19,470 --> 00:34:21,319
With the perspective I have now,

857
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:22,429
I want to reflect

858
00:34:22,430 --> 00:34:24,390
on the hits and misses.

859
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:26,159
But you know,

860
00:34:26,160 --> 00:34:27,319
looking back,

861
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,469
my views on a lot of things

862
00:34:28,470 --> 00:34:30,389
are very different from before.

863
00:34:30,390 --> 00:34:31,639
Like what, for example?

864
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:32,910
When I was younger,

865
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:35,029
I was restless.

866
00:34:35,030 --> 00:34:37,390
I always tried to settle things quickly.

867
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:39,069
But looking back now,

868
00:34:39,070 --> 00:34:40,549
a lot of those families

869
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:41,549
and relationships

870
00:34:41,550 --> 00:34:43,680
might not have been beyond saving.

871
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:48,589
I don't think you should
be so hard on yourself.

872
00:34:48,590 --> 00:34:51,199
Think about how many cases
we handle every year.

873
00:34:51,200 --> 00:34:52,109
Is there any case

874
00:34:52,110 --> 00:34:54,029
where we didn't try our best to mediate?

875
00:34:54,030 --> 00:34:55,989
Every decision was a balance

876
00:34:55,990 --> 00:34:57,350
of law and compassion.

877
00:34:57,390 --> 00:34:58,870
You're right.

878
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:00,589
Besides,

879
00:35:00,590 --> 00:35:01,639
times are different now.

880
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:04,120
The judicial system
is constantly evolving.

881
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:06,029
But the workload for everyone

882
00:35:06,030 --> 00:35:08,239
is only getting heavier.

883
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:09,639
You have a lot more on your plate

884
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,680
than we ever did back then.

885
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:12,759
If you demand

886
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:14,679
absolute perfection from yourself,

887
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:16,040
you'll just burn out.

888
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:19,000
It's just that I do have some regrets

889
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,600
with some of those cases.

890
00:35:21,510 --> 00:35:22,069
Oh, right.

891
00:35:22,070 --> 00:35:23,879
Speaking of pressure,

892
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:24,799
I just thought of something.

893
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:27,429
It's been on my mind for a while now.

894
00:35:27,430 --> 00:35:29,480
Why keep it to yourself? Tell me.

895
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,589
I'm just a little worried, you know?

896
00:35:31,590 --> 00:35:32,949
But then again,

897
00:35:32,950 --> 00:35:34,389
I'm just an outsider.

898
00:35:34,390 --> 00:35:36,910
It's not really my place to say much.

899
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:39,359
But of course, with you,

900
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,589
I don't have to hide anything.

901
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:42,389
I'll just be blunt, so just listen.

902
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:43,759
Ever since Tong left the hospital,

903
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:48,560
I feel like Shu Jing has been
too overprotective with the kids.

904
00:35:48,950 --> 00:35:51,830
She blames herself for
what happened to Tong

905
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:54,080
and for the way Fei has changed.

906
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:57,270
She's not in a good headspace.

907
00:36:09,030 --> 00:36:11,389
See that tree on the far right?

908
00:36:11,390 --> 00:36:12,350
Look.

909
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,600
She hasn't moved an inch.

910
00:36:14,950 --> 00:36:16,279
I wish she'd at least

911
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:18,040
sway those branches a little.

912
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,239
We should be glad

913
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:21,040
she's even on stage.

914
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,880
(Jointly Owned)

915
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,520
(Unknown Number)

916
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:42,840
(Unknown Number)

917
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:54,790
Is this Shu Jing?

918
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,520
Who's calling?

919
00:36:56,550 --> 00:36:58,640
I'm the driver delivering your order.

920
00:36:58,760 --> 00:36:59,719
You ordered a dresser

921
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,430
from the mall, right?

922
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:03,830
You live in the Longqi Bay complex,

923
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:05,790
Unit 2,

924
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,029
Apartment 803.

925
00:37:07,030 --> 00:37:08,560
Is that correct, Judge Shu?

926
00:37:09,950 --> 00:37:11,750
How do you know I'm a judge?

927
00:37:12,550 --> 00:37:14,270
I just happened to get your delivery.

928
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:15,319
Talk about a coincidence.

929
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,429
I'm Zhao Xinmin.

930
00:37:16,430 --> 00:37:18,279
My wife is Li Mingming.

931
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:19,589
And your father is Zhao Jianguo.

932
00:37:19,590 --> 00:37:21,469
Exactly. You remember now.

933
00:37:21,470 --> 00:37:22,680
Judge Shu,

934
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:24,120
this whole thing is

935
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:25,839
actually pretty complicated.

936
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:26,949
It's not something

937
00:37:26,950 --> 00:37:28,319
I can explain over the phone.

938
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:30,790
Let's grab dinner
and talk about it in person.

939
00:37:30,950 --> 00:37:32,279
What's so complicated about it?

940
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:33,359
Your only request is

941
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,159
for your parents' property to go to you.

942
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,870
Just wait for the verdict.

943
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:39,710
Don't ever contact me privately again.

944
00:37:41,070 --> 00:37:43,200
Another report
for the discipline committee.

945
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:58,000
Where's Fei?

946
00:38:00,430 --> 00:38:03,520
She must be tired
and crawled back inside.

947
00:38:09,390 --> 00:38:10,640
There's no one in the tree.

948
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:19,000
Fei!

949
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,200
Fei!

950
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:26,870
Judge Shen.

951
00:38:28,990 --> 00:38:30,639
You're finally heading to your car.

952
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:31,589
Just finished work?

953
00:38:31,590 --> 00:38:32,679
Have you eaten yet?

954
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:34,839
My grandmother sent these
from my hometown.

955
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,120
They're delicious.

956
00:38:41,030 --> 00:38:42,159
I appreciate the thought,

957
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,790
but I don't have a sweet tooth.

958
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:44,989
It's just a small token.

959
00:38:44,990 --> 00:38:46,589
They're cheap, so please take them.

960
00:38:46,590 --> 00:38:49,109
If you won't eat them,
share them with your colleagues.

961
00:38:49,110 --> 00:38:51,560
Go on, they aren't worth much.

962
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:55,480
Thank you.

963
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,270
I'm the one who should be thanking you.

964
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:00,680
Judge Shen,

965
00:39:01,030 --> 00:39:02,109
you know,

966
00:39:02,110 --> 00:39:04,359
I'll never forget
that you saved my life.

967
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:06,319
And the way you helped Feng Shengli,

968
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,480
I honestly don't know how to repay you.

969
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:11,080
I know you said
I shouldn't bring it up again,

970
00:39:11,430 --> 00:39:14,109
but I was wondering if you could
help me one more time

971
00:39:14,110 --> 00:39:15,549
with Ms. Ding's case.

972
00:39:15,550 --> 00:39:16,879
She really needs to move it up,

973
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,430
like I mentioned before.

974
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:27,949
Hello, Xiang Hui.

975
00:39:27,950 --> 00:39:29,589
Judge Shen, where are you right now?

976
00:39:29,590 --> 00:39:31,109
Just finished work. Why?

977
00:39:31,110 --> 00:39:33,199
Haven't you checked the group?
Fei is missing.

978
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:35,069
We're heading to the theater
to help with the search.

979
00:39:35,070 --> 00:39:35,839
Can you make it?

980
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,870
Alright, I'm on my way.

981
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:39,790
Wait.

982
00:39:44,030 --> 00:39:45,310
Never mind.

983
00:39:45,510 --> 00:39:46,509
They found her?

984
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:47,750
No.

985
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,029
Le said

986
00:39:49,030 --> 00:39:50,680
Tong just sent a message.

987
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,429
She claims she's kidnapped Fei.

988
00:39:52,430 --> 00:39:54,080
Fei was kidnapped?

989
00:39:58,590 --> 00:40:01,000
(Honorable Judge Shu Jing,)

990
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,680
(we meet again.)

991
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:04,750
By the time you see this video,

992
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:07,430
your precious daughter, Fei,

993
00:40:07,550 --> 00:40:09,390
will be right here with me.

994
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:12,200
Like I told you the last time we met,

995
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:13,680
one day,

996
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:15,589
I'll to make everyone

997
00:40:15,590 --> 00:40:17,159
who looked down on me and my mom

998
00:40:17,160 --> 00:40:18,389
pay the price.

999
00:40:18,390 --> 00:40:19,910
You're the first.

1000
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:23,469
I'll even throw in a little gift.

1001
00:40:23,470 --> 00:40:25,830
Proof that your husband assaulted me.

1002
00:40:27,070 --> 00:40:28,239
He has a red birthmark

1003
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:29,759
right on his neck.

1004
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,430
Surely you haven't forgotten.

1005
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,389
You two were in this together
from the start.

1006
00:40:33,390 --> 00:40:35,109
Did you ever think this day would come?

1007
00:40:35,110 --> 00:40:36,640
Tell me,

1008
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,160
do you regret it now?

1009
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:41,559
(Tong is coming after me this time.)

1010
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:44,279
(Tianhai Public Safety Command Center)
(Wasn't that case cleared a long time ago?)

1011
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:46,029
(Why won't she just let it go?)

1012
00:40:46,030 --> 00:40:47,389
(Outside Qi Xin Tian)
(To Tong,)

1013
00:40:47,390 --> 00:40:50,000
(judges and cops are all just the same.)

1014
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:52,359
She's out for revenge in her own way.

1015
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:54,029
(She just mentioned)

1016
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:55,640
(a red birthmark on his neck.)

1017
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:56,480
(What was that about?)

1018
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,839
(It's probably just her imagination.)

1019
00:40:57,840 --> 00:41:00,279
(The doctor said her PTSD)

1020
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:02,000
(causes false memories.)

1021
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:02,949
(Lian has never)

1022
00:41:02,950 --> 00:41:04,759
(had a birthmark on his neck.)

1023
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:05,879
(Wait, I remember now.)

1024
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,509
(I really did have
a red mark on my neck.)

1025
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:09,469
(It was the morning Tong disappeared.)

1026
00:41:09,470 --> 00:41:11,199
(I ran into her at the door)

1027
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:13,560
(as she was heading to school.)

1028
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:15,839
(I definitely had a red mark that day.)

1029
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,949
(But it wasn't a birthmark.)

1030
00:41:16,950 --> 00:41:18,549
(It was your lipstick.)

1031
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:20,120
(So you're saying)

1032
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:21,799
(she mistook a lipstick stain)

1033
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:23,029
(for a birthmark?)

1034
00:41:23,030 --> 00:41:23,469
(Exactly.)

1035
00:41:23,470 --> 00:41:24,879
(I was in such a rush to leave,)

1036
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:26,589
(she must have seen it.)

1037
00:41:26,590 --> 00:41:27,509
(When I got to work,)

1038
00:41:27,510 --> 00:41:29,989
(everyone was making fun of me for it.)

1039
00:41:29,990 --> 00:41:32,480
(That's why it sticks in my mind.)

1040
00:41:32,550 --> 00:41:33,909
(And then that night,)

1041
00:41:33,910 --> 00:41:35,319
(she disappeared.)

1042
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,839
(I never understood)

1043
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:39,199
(why she was so sure it was me.)

1044
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:41,270
(It had to be because of that red mark.)

1045
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,639
(So,)

1046
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,589
(the actual killer)

1047
00:41:43,590 --> 00:41:45,389
(has a red mark on his neck.)

1048
00:41:45,390 --> 00:41:47,080
(This lead is vital.)

1049
00:41:47,470 --> 00:41:48,109
(There were)

1050
00:41:48,110 --> 00:41:50,109
(violent attacks on young girls.)

1051
00:41:50,110 --> 00:41:52,199
(The timing, locations,)

1052
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:52,949
(and the MO)

1053
00:41:52,950 --> 00:41:54,029
(are all identical.)

1054
00:41:54,030 --> 00:41:55,830
(It's clearly the same person.)

1055
00:41:56,200 --> 00:41:57,589
(But he's incredibly cunning.)

1056
00:41:57,590 --> 00:41:59,429
(He cleans the crime scenes every time.)

1057
00:41:59,430 --> 00:42:01,359
(He definitely knows how to evade us.)

1058
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:03,429
(Plus, without any eyewitnesses,)

1059
00:42:03,430 --> 00:42:05,549
(the case was at a dead end.)

1060
00:42:05,550 --> 00:42:07,069
(Now we finally have a breakthrough.)

1061
00:42:07,070 --> 00:42:08,589
(This red mark)

1062
00:42:08,590 --> 00:42:10,239
(is the key to identifying the culprit.)

1063
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:11,279
(Finding the culprit)

1064
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,910
(is the only way Tong will find peace.)

1065
00:42:12,990 --> 00:42:14,750
(Try not to worry too much.)

1066
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:17,830
(Footage shows
the girls are still in the city.)

1067
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:20,239
(We've tightened security
at all transit hubs.)

1068
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:21,319
(I believe)

1069
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:23,000
(we'll find them soon.)

1070
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:27,600
(Police)
Knowing Tong,

1071
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:29,870
she might be obsessive,

1072
00:42:30,030 --> 00:42:32,000
but not enough to hurt Fei.

1073
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:34,679
They've been inseparable
since childhood.

1074
00:42:34,680 --> 00:42:36,600
They're closer than sisters.

1075
00:42:37,030 --> 00:42:37,879
Right now,

1076
00:42:37,880 --> 00:42:40,239
Tong is likely just
using Fei as leverage.

1077
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:41,520
I know.

1078
00:42:45,910 --> 00:42:47,710
She wants to
force a confession out of me.

1079
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:49,199
She's using Fei's safety

1080
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,589
to break my spirit.

1081
00:42:50,590 --> 00:42:51,719
But she'd never

1082
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:53,870
actually hurt her.

1083
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:55,759
That's why we have to stay calm.

1084
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:57,080
Don't panic.

1085
00:42:58,070 --> 00:42:59,230
Look,

1086
00:42:59,590 --> 00:43:01,000
let me take you home.

1087
00:43:01,430 --> 00:43:03,160
You need to get some rest.

1088
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1089
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1090
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1091
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1092
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1093
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1094
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1095
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1096
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1097
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1098
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1099
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1100
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1101
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1102
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1103
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1104
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1105
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1106
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1107
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1108
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1109
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1110
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1111
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1112
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1113
